{
  "DNA Structure": "DNA结构",
  "This lesson covers the fundamental measures of center used to analyze and summarize data sets. You'll learn how to calculate and apply the mean, median, and mode, and understand when each is most appropriate.": "这个课程涵盖了分析和总结数据集的中心的基本测量方法。 您将学会如何计算和应用平均值、 中位数和模式, 并了解何时最合适 。",
  "What is biotechnology?": "什么是生物技术?",
  "Biotechnology is the broad field of using living organisms, cells, or biological systems to develop products and technologies that benefit humans. Examples include using bacteria to produce medicines, engineering crops for better nutrition, DNA fingerprinting in forensics, and using enzymes in industrial processes. It combines biology with technology across medicine, agriculture, and industry.": "生物技术是利用生物机体、细胞或生物系统开发有利于人类的产品和技术的广泛领域,例如利用细菌生产药物、为更好的营养而工程作物、法医鉴定中的DNA指纹和工业过程中使用酶,将生物学与医学、农业和工业的技术结合起来。",
  "What is recombinant DNA?": "什么是重组DNA?",
  "Recombinant DNA (rDNA) is formed by joining DNA fragments from different organisms — for example, inserting a human gene into a bacterial plasmid. This technique, developed in the 1970s by Cohen and Boyer, is the foundation of genetic engineering. It allows scientists to produce human proteins in bacteria (like insulin), create transgenic organisms, and study gene function.": "重组DNA(rDNA)是结合不同生物体的DNA碎片形成的,例如,将人类基因插入细菌囊中。 1970年代由科恩和博伊尔开发的这一技术是基因工程的基础。 它使科学家可以在细菌中产生人类蛋白(如胰岛素 ) , 创造转基因生物并研究基因功能。",
  "What is a transgenic organism?": "什么是转基因生物?",
  "A transgenic organism carries DNA from a different species that was introduced through genetic engineering. Examples include Bt corn (containing a bacterial gene for insect resistance), Golden Rice (containing daffodil and bacterial genes for beta-carotene production), and transgenic goats that produce human proteins in their milk. The foreign gene is called a transgene.": "转基因生物携带通过基因工程引进的不同物种的DNA,例如Bt玉米(含有抗昆虫细菌基因)、Golden Rice(含有用于生产β-甲状腺素的甲草胺和细菌基因)和在母乳中产生人类蛋白质的转基因山羊。",
  "What is gene therapy?": "什么是基因疗法?",
  "Gene therapy aims to treat or cure genetic diseases by addressing the root cause — the faulty gene itself. Methods include inserting a functional copy of a defective gene, editing a mutated gene to restore its function, or silencing a harmful gene. Delivery methods use vectors (often modified viruses) to carry the therapeutic gene into the patient's cells. While promising, it carries risks such as immune reactions and insertional mutagenesis.": "基因疗法的目的是通过解决根本原因——缺陷基因本身——来治疗或治愈基因疾病,方法包括插入缺陷基因的功能复制件,编辑变异基因以恢复其功能,或压制有害基因,施药方法使用病媒(经常变异病毒)将治疗基因带入病人的细胞,虽然很有希望,但带有免疫反应和插入突变等风险。",
  "What is a plasmid?": "什么是金字塔?",
  "Plasmids are small, circular, double-stranded DNA molecules that replicate independently of the bacterial chromosome. They naturally carry genes that benefit bacteria (such as antibiotic resistance). In genetic engineering, plasmids are used as vectors — scientists insert a gene of interest into the plasmid, then introduce it into bacteria. The bacteria replicate the plasmid along with the foreign gene, producing the desired protein.": "等离子体是小的、循环的、双层的DNA分子,它们独立于细菌染色体而复制。它们自然含有有利于细菌的基因(如抗生素抗药性 ) 。 在遗传工程中,粒子被用作矢量 — — 科学家们在质子中插入了一种感兴趣的基因,然后将其引入细菌。细菌将质子和外国基因一起复制,产生理想的蛋白质。",
  "What is bioinformatics?": "什么是生物信息学?",
  "Bioinformatics is an interdisciplinary field that combines biology, computer science, and statistics to collect, store, and analyze large biological datasets. It is indispensable for genome sequencing projects (like the Human Genome Project), comparing DNA sequences across species, predicting protein structures, tracking disease outbreaks, and identifying drug targets. Without bioinformatics, analyzing the billions of base pairs in a human genome would be impossible.": "生物信息学是一个跨学科领域,结合生物学、计算机科学和统计收集、储存和分析大型生物数据集。 这对于基因组测序项目(如人类基因组项目 ) 、 比较不同物种的DNA序列、预测蛋白结构、跟踪疾病爆发和确定毒品目标都是必不可少的。 没有生物信息学,分析人类基因组数十亿对基对是不可能的。",
  "What is a 'vector' in the context of genetic engineering?": "在遗传工程方面,什么是“矢量”?",
  "In genetic engineering, a vector is a DNA molecule used to carry a foreign gene into a host cell. The most common vectors are bacterial plasmids (small circular DNA molecules) and modified viruses. A good vector must be able to replicate inside the host, carry the gene of interest, and include selectable markers (like antibiotic resistance) to identify cells that successfully took up the vector.": "在遗传工程中,矢量是一种DNA分子,用于将外国基因带入宿主细胞。最常见的矢量是细菌粒子(小型循环DNA分子)和改良病毒。好的矢量必须能够在宿主内部复制,携带感兴趣的基因,并包括可选标记(如抗生素抗药性),以识别成功吸收矢量的细胞。",
  "What is a GMO (Genetically Modified Organism)?": "什么是转基因生物(转基因生物)?",
  "A GMO is an organism whose genetic material has been altered using genetic engineering — not through natural reproduction or traditional breeding. Examples include Bt corn (with a bacterial gene for insect resistance), Golden Rice (engineered for vitamin A production), and bacteria engineered to produce human insulin. GMOs are regulated by agencies like the FDA, EPA, and USDA, and remain subject to public debate regarding safety, labeling, and environmental impact.": "转基因生物是一种生物,其遗传材料不是通过自然繁殖或传统繁殖,而是通过基因工程改变的,例如Bt玉米(含有抗昆虫细菌基因)、Golden Rice(为生产维生素A而设计)和细菌(为生产人类胰岛素而设计),转基因生物受林业发展局、美国环保局和美国农业部等机构管制,并仍然受到关于安全、标签和环境影响的公开辩论。",
  "What is bioremediation?": "什么是生物补救?",
  "Bioremediation uses microorganisms (bacteria, fungi) or plants (phytoremediation) to detoxify contaminated environments. Bacteria can metabolize oil spills, heavy metals, pesticides, and industrial solvents. For example, after the Deepwater Horizon spill, oil-degrading bacteria like Alcanivorax borkumensis helped break down hydrocarbons. Bioremediation is often cheaper, less disruptive, and more environmentally friendly than physical or chemical cleanup methods.": "生物补救利用微生物(细菌、真菌)或植物(植物补救)来解除受污染环境的毒性。细菌可以代谢石油溢漏、重金属、杀虫剂和工业溶剂。例如,在深水地平线溢出后,Alcanivorax borkumensis等石油降解细菌有助于打破碳氢化合物。生物补救往往更便宜,破坏性更小,比物理或化学清理方法更环保。",
  "What is gel electrophoresis used for?": "凝胶电极是用来做什么的?",
  "Gel electrophoresis separates macromolecules by size. DNA fragments are loaded into wells in an agarose or polyacrylamide gel, and an electric field drives them through the gel matrix. Smaller molecules migrate faster and farther. Scientists use this to analyze restriction digests, verify PCR products, compare DNA profiles in forensics, and assess the purity of protein preparations. A size standard (ladder) run alongside allows estimation of fragment sizes.": "Gel 电极按大小将大型分子分开。 DNA碎片被装入水井,装在藻类或聚丙烯酰胺凝胶中,一个电场驱动着它们穿过凝胶基体。 较小的分子迁移得更快、更远。 科学家用这个分析限制摘要,核查PCR产品,在法医中比较DNA特征,并评估蛋白制剂的纯度。 大小标准( ladder) 与 碎片大小一起运行, 允许对碎片大小进行估计 。",
  "What is pharmacogenomics?": "什么是药理工程学?",
  "Pharmacogenomics combines pharmacology and genomics to understand how genetic variation influences drug efficacy and toxicity. For example, variations in the CYP2D6 enzyme gene affect how quickly patients metabolize drugs like codeine — ultra-rapid metabolizers risk overdose while poor metabolizers get no benefit. This field is driving the shift from 'one-size-fits-all' dosing to precision medicine, where drug choice and dosage are tailored to a patient's genetic profile.": "例如,CYP2D6酶基因的变异影响病人如何快速地新陈代谢药物,如可待因——超快速新陈代谢剂风险过大,而贫乏的代谢剂却得不到任何好处。这个领域正在推动从“一刀切”剂量转向精密药物,药物选择和剂量根据病人的基因特征而定制。",
  "What is somatic cell nuclear transfer (SCNT)?": "什么是体细胞核转移?",
  "SCNT is the technique used to clone Dolly the sheep in 1996. The process involves: (1) removing the nucleus from an egg cell (enucleation), (2) inserting the nucleus from an adult somatic cell into the enucleated egg, and (3) stimulating the reconstructed cell to divide and develop. The resulting organism is genetically identical to the nucleus donor. SCNT raises questions about telomere length, epigenetic reprogramming, and the ethics of reproductive cloning.": "SCNT是1996年用于克隆Dolly羊的技术,过程包括:(1) 从卵细胞中取出核(割除),(2) 从成人体细胞中将核插入卵中,(3) 刺激重建后的细胞分裂和发育,由此形成的有机体在遗传上与核捐献者相同。",
  "What is a gene drive?": "什么是基因驱动?",
  "A gene drive uses CRISPR technology to bias inheritance so that a genetic modification is passed to nearly 100% of offspring instead of the usual 50% (Mendelian inheritance). This means the modification can spread through an entire wild population in just a few generations. Proposed applications include making mosquitoes unable to transmit malaria. The major concern is irreversibility — once released, gene drives would be extremely difficult or impossible to recall if unintended consequences emerge.": "基因驱动器利用CRISPR技术来偏见遗产继承,使基因改变传递给近100%的后代,而不是通常的50%(Mendelian继承),这意味着这种改变可以在几代人的时间里传播到整个野生人口中,拟议的应用包括使蚊虫无法传播疟疾,主要的关切是不可逆转性——一旦释放,基因驱动器将极难或无法回忆是否出现意想不到的后果。",
  "After the Deepwater Horizon oil spill, scientists applied oil-eating bacteria to contaminated beaches. Over several months, hydrocarbon levels dropped significantly. Explain this biotechnology application and its advantages over traditional cleanup.": "在深水地平线石油泄漏事件之后,科学家们将食油细菌应用到污染海滩上,几个月来碳氢化合物含量大幅下降,解释了生物技术的应用及其优于传统清理的优势。",
  "Bioremediation uses living organisms to degrade environmental pollutants. After the 2010 Deepwater Horizon spill (the largest marine oil spill in history), both naturally occurring and deliberately applied (bioaugmented) oil-degrading bacteria helped break down hydrocarbons. These bacteria possess enzymes that oxidize petroleum compounds, using them as metabolic fuel. Advantages over traditional methods include cost-effectiveness, ability to treat subsurface contamination inaccessible to skimmers, production of harmless byproducts, and reduced secondary environmental damage.": "在2010年深水地平线溢出(历史上最大的海洋石油溢出)之后,自然发生并故意应用(生物放大)石油降解细菌,这些细菌拥有氧化石油化合物的酶,将其作为代谢燃料使用,这些细菌拥有使石油化合物氧化的酶,传统方法的优点包括成本效益、处理下层污染的能力,而滑雪者无法接触这些污染、无害副产品的生产以及减少二次环境损害。",
  "Dolly the sheep was cloned via SCNT using a nucleus from a 6-year-old ewe's mammary cell. She developed arthritis, lung disease, and was euthanized at age 6 (normal lifespan: 10-12 years). Explain the biological basis for premature aging in cloned animals.": "Dolly 羊被克隆为通过SCNT克隆的 SCNT , 使用了6岁幼崽哺乳细胞的核心。 她患了关节炎、肺病,并在6岁(正常寿命:10-12岁)时被安乐化了。 解释克隆动物过早老龄化的生物基础。",
  "Two key factors explain premature aging in clones: (1) Telomere shortening — telomeres are protective DNA caps that shorten with each cell division. Dolly's donor cell came from a 6-year-old sheep, meaning its telomeres were already shortened. Dolly's cells inherited this shorter starting length, potentially limiting their replicative lifespan. (2) Epigenetic reprogramming failure — the donor nucleus must be 'reset' to an embryonic state, but this process is often incomplete, leading to abnormal DNA methylation patterns and gene expression. Together, these factors increase susceptibility to arthritis, cancer, and organ failure in cloned animals.": "造成克隆人过早老化的两个关键因素:(1) 泰罗美缩短—— 泰罗美是保护性DNA帽,与每个细胞部隔得很短;多莉的捐献细胞来自一只6岁的绵羊,这意味着它的滴球已经缩短;多莉的细胞继承了这么短的起始长度,有可能限制其复制寿命;(2) 发基因重新规划失败—— 捐赠者核心必须“重新设置”到胚胎状态,但这一过程往往不完整,导致DNA异常的甲基化模式和基因表达;这些因素加在一起,增加了对关节炎、癌症和克隆动物器官衰竭的易受感染性。",
  "Bt corn produces an insecticidal protein from Bacillus thuringiensis. After 10 years of exclusive Bt corn planting, a farmer notices some corn borers surviving. Explain the evolutionary mechanism and the management strategy designed to prevent this outcome.": "Bt玉米生产一种来自Bacillus Turviensis的杀虫蛋白。 经过10年的纯种Bt玉米种植,农民注意到一些玉米育种者幸存下来。解释进化机制以及旨在防止这一结果的管理战略。",
  "This is a real-world example of natural selection. In any large insect population, genetic variation means some individuals carry alleles (e.g., mutations in midgut Bt-toxin receptors) that confer partial resistance. When Bt crops are the only food source, susceptible insects die while resistant ones survive and reproduce, increasing resistance allele frequency over generations. The 'refuge strategy' (planting 20-50% non-Bt crops) maintains a large population of susceptible insects that mate with rare resistant individuals, keeping resistance alleles at low frequency through dilution. This is mandatory under EPA regulations for all Bt crop growers.": "这是自然选择的一个真实世界例子。 在任何大的昆虫群中,遗传变异意味着某些人携带产生部分抗药性的异象(例如,中突变的Bt-toxin受体),当Bt作物是唯一的食物来源时,易受感染的昆虫在抗药性昆虫生存和繁殖的同时死亡,从而在几代人中增加抗药性。“救济战略”(种植20-50%的非Bt作物)维持着大量易受感染的昆虫,这些昆虫与罕见的抗药性人结合,通过稀释保持低频抗药性。根据环保局的条例,这对所有Bt作物种植者都是强制性的。"
}